# Machine-wide git excludes — XDG global excludesfile ($XDG_CONFIG_HOME/git/ignore).
# Active for every repo on this machine (git reads this path by default when
# core.excludesfile is unset). Holds OS/tool cruft that should never be committed
# from anywhere. Per-repo .gitignore still carries project-specific rules (and a
# belt-and-suspenders .DS_Store for collaborators who don't share this file).
#
# Deliberately omits IDE project dirs (.idea/, .vscode/): some repos selectively
# commit files under them, and a directory-level ignore here would block those
# re-includes. Those stay per-repo.

# --- macOS ---
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
.fseventsd
.DocumentRevisions-V100
.TemporaryItems
.VolumeIcon.icns
.com.apple.timemachine.donotpresent
.apdisk

# --- Windows (shared drives / collaborators) ---
Thumbs.db
Thumbs.db:encryptable
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

# --- Linux ---
.directory
.Trash-*

# --- Editor swap / backup / lock files (never meaningful to commit) ---
*~
*.swp
*.swo
*.swn
\#*\#
.#*

# --- Claude Code (machine-local agent state) ---
**/.claude/settings.local.json
# Parallel-session worktrees Claude Code (and clc) create under .claude/worktrees/.
# These are linked git worktrees of the repo itself — never their own commit in the
# outer repo — so keep them off git's radar everywhere. In a clc-enrolled repo the
# whole .claude/ tree is already locally excluded, so this is a harmless no-op there.
**/.claude/worktrees/
